President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Oregon due to severe winter storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from January 7 to January 10, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Columbia, Deschutes, Hood River, and Josephine are eligible for federal funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Willie G. Nunn has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.